{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Gn6pQ8yKc2UnhmPpp1A73Q","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three verification checks pass:\n\n1. **Cluster health: green** — all shards assigned, `active_shards_percent: 100%`\n2. **All 3 nodes present** — `es-cluster-0`, `es-cluster-1`, `es-cluster-2` all appear in `/_cat/nodes`\n3. **`app-data` readable** — returns the original `{\"msg\":\"seed\"}` document\n\n**What was wrong and what was fixed:**\n\nThe precondition injected two bugs into the `es-config` ConfigMap via a heredoc that shell-evaluated `${POD_NAME}` to empty:\n- `node.name:` was blank → `es-cluster-2` crashed immediately on start with a parse error\n- `discovery.seed_hosts` used `default.svc.cluster.local` instead of the correct headless service address (short names like `es-cluster-0.es-cluster`)\n\n**Fix steps:**\n1. Restored the ConfigMap with `node.name: ${POD_NAME}` (literal, for ES to substitute) and correct short-name seed hosts\n2. Deleted the crashing `es-cluster-2` pod so the StatefulSet recreated it with the fixed config — it joined the cluster\n3. Force-allocated the stale primary shard on `es-cluster-0` via `_cluster/reroute allocate_stale_primary` to recover from the `no_valid_shard_copy` state left by the old pod's PVC deletion; the replica was then automatically assigned to `es-cluster-2`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":658,"cache_read_input_tokens":44780,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":658},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6483a7ea-fae9-41bb-afcf-26ff534f4665","uuid":"d7bc6690-90ec-4b43-b6da-10ced15826f5","request_id":"req_011CbyCEXtDQkJMY5a6nJokq"}
